cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper describes a method for detecting cars in X-ray cargo images using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for training the model falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of oversampling to address the low number of car images available for training, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
